I forgot what lvl the last upgrade is but lets just assume lvl 50.<br />
Shocking grasp<br />
9m range <br />
(range goes up by 1m per rank)<br />
1 minute recast<br />
(needed to avoid abuse for energy regen)<br />
Drains 25end/s and returns 200 energy/s while active<br />
(energy regen is for mimic finisher)<br />
Deals 750 dmg /s <br />
(not counting int/sdf this would be it's base, with 135% int/20% sdf it would go up to 1150/s)<br />
Roots offensive target<br />
Roots caster<br />
<br />
This would allow solo sorc could root a target for 4 seconds with no +end mods and a full bar of END.<br />
This would also return 800 mana (since most dont use it to save END for GE)<br />
This would end up dealing 4600 dmg @lvl 50 for the av sorc over 4s (since most wanted to use it as a sort of finish mob off type of deal) which is 1150dps, and Rooting the mob helps the &quot;finish off&quot; mentality.<br />
This would be useable outside of mele range to be safe to use in more situations (9M range)<br />
This would still allow for mimic use (since base is simmilar to CV you would end up with a mimic about what cv does)<br />
<br />
<br />
now lets factor in a max regen setting<br />
ageless robe + two +1 end rings, + clr end buff (9+6+10=25 end regen per tick)<br />
and you can maintain it for 6s, return 1200 energy, and deal 6900 dmg.<br />
<br />
The high (25/s) end cost is needed because with it at 20/s you could maintain it for 12 seconds and return 2400 energy and deal 13,800 dmg (a bit TOO good if you ask me)<br />
<br />
Now If I had a spell like this In my arsenal I'd definately want to use it every fight when the mob is nearly dead.<br />
<br />
I think the costs could use some tweaking, but thats how I'd like to see the spell end up
			
