		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
I've actually started up some polls on the TTH forum to see what peoples reactions would be (seperate poll in each class's section) if the developers followed their design goal for the offensive casters, which is roughly:<br />
<br />
Equivilant damage across the archetype, each class dealing / contributing damage differently, and each class having valid and diverse secondary roles.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
The way i <i>PERSONALLY </i>see it, a 30 second fight should be where the sorcerer allways wins out as the best dps since they have the strongest burst damage potiential. Then in second i would say the psionicist and druid should match up with the sorcerer at 45 seconds, and the necro should pass up all 3 classes past the 60 second mark, and maintain this lead by just a tiny bit (10% or less).<br />
<br />
But, if you add in all the buffs and enhancements that you will recieve, the sorcerer will likely pull ahead by 10-15% by comparison to the other casters, making them &quot;the best&quot; damage potiential, as nukes can be enhanced MUCH better than dots or pets, which the other 3 classes rely on.<br />
<br />
<br />
To me this would be fair, sorcerer is still on top, they would get a greatly valued and more functional secondary role, and would stop being eq1 wizard 2.0, and would be the Vanguard sorcerer. Hell, if they wanted they could give us some <u>incredibly </u>strong hex debuffs that would cripple a target's resistances, allowing for our spells to hit more, as well as for our group to do more damage.<br />
<br />
Also, this allows the psionicist class to be less of the eq1 enchanter 2.0 and more of the vanguard psionicist, a heavy damage dealing class with cc/enhancement as their secondary function.<br />
<br />
<br />
Imo its healthier for all classes involved and it takes us away from the sterotypical, arcaic concepts of the eq1 classes. We dont need a &quot;best&quot; dps class or a &quot;cc class&quot; (as thats all they do and if they cant CC their worth is highly deminished)<br />
<br />
<br />
And actually, if all you plan on playing is a sorcerer as your main, of what concern is another classes dps to you? It wont directly effect your personal gameplay unless you PUG, or dare i say it, PUR (oh the stories lol)?<br />
<br />
<br />
Unless someone can come up we an adequte reason why the other <i>offensive</i> casters shouldnt match Sorc dps past a certain point in a fight, then i honestly dont see what the issue would be with enhancing the other caster's dps, unless its just some ego thing...
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
